<a href="#0" id="0">We conducted an error analysis to attribute errors to either step when the system detects a wrong set of corrections for a sentence.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">We examine the first step ’ s output.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">If the resulting basic edits do not match with those that compose the actual corrections, we attribute the error to the first step.</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">Otherwise, we attribute the error to the second step.</a>
<a href="#4" id="4">Our analysis confirms that the merging step is the bottleneck in the current correction detection system – it accounts for 75% of the mis-detections.</a>
